article.headline: Delaware 74, George Mason 65
article.story: NEWARK, Del. (AP) -- Senior guard Mike Ames scored nine of his team-high 22 points in the first four minutes of the second half as the University of Delaware defeated George Mason 74-65 Wednesday night. Delaware (11-7, 5-4 Colonial Athletic Association) is 5-0 in home league games this season. The Blue Hens shot 51 percent from the field (28 of 55) and matched a season-low 10 turnovers. Ames sank four of five three-point attempts. He has 207 career three-pointers, four short of the Delaware record. Mike Slattery, Herb Courtney and Lebo Maepa added nine points each for the Blue Hens, with Slattery dishing out eight assists and Maepa coming off the bench to grab a team-high six rebounds. George Mason (12-6, 5-4), lost its second straight game despite an effort from forward Jai Lewis, who hit on 10 of 12 shots from the field to finish with a career-high 26 points to go with nine rebounds. Lamar Butler came off the bench to add 12 points, Trent Wurtz added 10 points and eight rebounds off the bench, Mark Davis chipped in with 10 points, and Terry Reynolds dished out 11 assists. The Patriots controlled the boards by a 40-29 margin but were hurt by 22 turnovers, including seven in a two-minute stretch early in the second half.
